 thought of this rich vein of scholarship and an afterword in which he applies both interpretive methods to the vexing question of the authorship of the Inner Chapters of the Zhuangzi. The Contemplative Foundations of Classical Daoism brings to fruition the cumulative investigations and observations of a leading figure in the emerging field of contemplative studies as they pertain to a core component of early Chinese thought.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aMeditationxTaoism. 0aTaoism. 4aAsian Studies : Chinese Religion and Philosophy. 4aAsian Studies : Chinese Studies. 4aPhilosophy : Contemplative Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Mysticism. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Taoism. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Taoist.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848272940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438482729423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438482729/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles